      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Absolutely not; reducing your warfarin on your own is extremely dangerous because it bypasses critical safety checks and can lead to life-threatening blood clots. Your feeling fine does not mean your heart needs the protection, only that your current dose is keeping your INR within the precise range your doctor calculated for you. Given that your doctor has been rushed, rely on trusted telehealth services to confirm your dose immediately before making any changes yourself.",
